<item>
            <title>[LU-16715] Resolve genl_lock might_sleep bug</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16715</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In review of &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/fs/lustre-release/+/49516&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/fs/lustre-release/+/49516&lt;/a&gt; Oleg reported for his RHLE7 debug kernel a __might_sleep() with the genl_lock(). Examining this I believe this to be a bug in the Netlink layer for the RHEL7 kernel.&#160; I believe the upstream fix 707693c8a498697aa8db240b93eb76ec62e30892 will resolve this. To prove this I like to request patch 49516 to tested with a RHEL8 debug kernel. If that passes then we can try applying the above commit against the RHEL7 kernel.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Oleg&amp;#39;s RHEL7 debug kernel.</environment>
